# 🧠 OS Concept 1: Distributed Transactions Basics

## 1️⃣ Simple Idea

A transaction may involve:

👉 multiple databases/services across machines.

All must succeed together.

---

## 🧠 Real-World Analogy

Online shopping 🛒

Need all together:

* payment success
* inventory update
* order creation

If one fails:

👉 rollback everything.

---

## Problem

In distributed systems:

❌ network failures
❌ machine crashes
❌ delays

make transactions difficult.

---

## Common Solution

### Two-Phase Commit (2PC)

---

## Phase 1

Coordinator asks:

```text id="n7x3vk"
"Can you commit?"
```

---

## Phase 2

If all agree:

✔ commit

Else:

❌ rollback

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: Why distributed transactions are difficult?**

👉 Because failures and network issues can occur across multiple systems.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="2k9qwb"
All systems commit together or rollback
```

